              "type": "text",
              "left": 24,
              "top": 66,
              "width": 800,
              "height": 30,
              "rotate": 0,
              "content": "<p style='font-size:13px;color:#64748b;font-weight:500;'>Trading one crypto for another \u2014 no bank required</p>",
              "defaultFontName": "Inter",
              "defaultColor": "#64748b"
            },
            {
              "id": "esb-s1-body",
              "type": "text",
              "left": 24,
              "top": 120,
              "width": 950,
              "height": 260,
              "rotate": 0,
              "content": "<p style='font-size:17px;color:#cbd5e1;line-height:1.8;'><b style='color:#8b5cf6;'>Swapping</b> simply means exchanging one cryptocurrency for another. You have Bitcoin and want Ethereum? You swap. You have USDC and want XRP? You swap.</p><br/><p style='font-size:17px;color:#cbd5e1;line-height:1.8;'>There are two ways to swap: through a <b style='color:#f1f5f9;'>centralized exchange (CEX)</b> like Coinbase where a company matches buyers and sellers, or through a <b style='color:#f1f5f9;'>decentralized exchange (DEX)</b> where code does it automatically with no middleman.</p>",
              "defaultFontName": "Inter",
              "defaultColor": "#cbd5e1"
            },
            {
              "id": "esb-s1-box1",
              "type": "shape",
              "left": 24,
